“Sadly, a 13-year old boy who tested positive for COVID-19 has passed away, and our thoughts and condolences are with the family at this time,” King’s College Hospital said in a statement. LONDON - A 13-year-old boy in London who tested positive for coronavirus has died, a hospital said on Tuesday. “Sadly, a 13-year old boy who tested positive for COVID-19 has passed away, and our thoughts and condolences are with the family at this time,” King’s College Hospital said in a statement. “The death has been referred to the coroner and no further comment will be made.”